If LD_PRELOAD is not specified, libgsasl.so library is not getting picked up during dynamic linking via LD_LIBRARY_PATH
{code}
export LD_PRELOAD=/x/libgsasl-1.8.0/lib/libgsasl.so
{code}

Workaround: use static linking
{code}
cc  -shared -O2 -g -pipe -Wall -Wp,-D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 -fexceptions -fstack-protector --param=ssp-buffer-size=4 -m64 -mtune=generic -Wl,-E -Wl,-rpath,/x/libgsasl-1.8.0/lib/libgsasl.so.7.9.6 --unresolved-symbols=ignore-in-shared-libs xs/BSON.o xs/Cursor.o xs/Mongo.o xs/MongoClient.o xs/OID.o mongo_link.o perl_mongo.o /x/libgsasl-1.8.0/lib/libgsasl.so -o blib/arch/auto/MongoDB/MongoDB.so
{code}

Using $gt in the "find" method for tailable cursors is not working properly. Had to resort to $gte.

For instance, this won't work as expected:

my $cursor = $collection->find({_id => {'$gt' => $last_doc->{_id}}});

But this will work:

my $cursor = $collection->find({_id => {'$gte' => $last_doc->{_id}}});

This issue is observed when tailing cursors, but not for cursors in general.

